CRESCENT RIDGE LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Crescent Ridge LLC ("Crescent Ridge") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Crescent Ridge generating facility ("Crescent Ridge Facility").
The Crescent Ridge Facility is a wind generating facility located in Bureau County, Illinois. The Crescent Ridge Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Commonwealth Edison Company and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Crescent Ridge's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Crescent Ridge Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Crescent Ridge's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Crescent Ridge shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $221,384.77 The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $18,448.73
